author: dlr
msg: * subversion/mod_dav_svn/repos.c
(dav_svn_set_headers): Use ap_set_content_type() to write to
request_rec->content_type per its API contract, allowing the
AddOutputFilterByType directive to work correctly.
Patch by: Paul Querna

author: dlr

work which is not yet functional, and may end up being removed later

* subversion/tests/mod_dav_svn
New directory, with an ignore for *-test.

author: dlr
msg: * subversion/mod_dav_svn/repos.c

author: julianfoad
msg: Make "svn add" skip nonexistent items with a warning.  Use svn_cl__try to
simplify the handling of warnings.  This is part of issue #2030: "Errorful
targets should be skipped, not end the entire operation".
Patch by: Vivek C. <vivek@collab.net>
* subversion/clients/cmdline/add-cmd.c
(svn_cl__add): Warn if path not found; use svn_cl__try.
